.TH NELIX 1 "June 2026" "Nelix 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
nelix \- command-line wrapper for Nelix package manifests
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nelix
[\fB--json\fR]
.I COMMAND
[\fIARGS\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B nelix
runs Nelix manifest and profile operations from the command line.
It currently routes commands through Emacs batch mode and the installed
Nelix Elisp libraries.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B apply MANIFEST
Install packages missing from MANIFEST and apply declared pins.
.TP
.B audit MANIFEST
Report manifest/profile drift without mutating state.
.TP
.B sync MANIFEST [--prune]
Apply MANIFEST and optionally remove unmanaged profile entries.
.TP
.B prune-plan MANIFEST
Print the read-only prune plan for MANIFEST.
.TP
.B lock MANIFEST
Write the manifest lock file.
.TP
.B lock validate MANIFEST
Validate the manifest lockfile schema without mutating state.
.TP
.B lock diff MANIFEST
Report read-only manifest/import drift against the lockfile.
.TP
.B upgrade-plan [MANIFEST|NAME]
Print a read-only upgrade plan.
.TP
.B outdated [MANIFEST|NAME] [--backend BACKEND]
Print a read-only cross-backend outdated report.
.TP
.B upgrade [MANIFEST|NAME]
Upgrade all packages, a single profile element, or outdated rows declared
by MANIFEST through the selected backend.
.TP
.B list
List profile entries.
.TP
.B rollback [GENERATION]
Roll back the profile.
.TP
.B doctor
Print a read-only environment health report.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --json
Print normalized JSON output.
.TP
.B --help
Show command usage.
.TP
.B --version
Show wrapper version.
.SH AUTHOR
Nelix is maintained by the Nelix contributors.
